article.headline: Green Bay 74, Cleveland St. 57
article.story: GREEN BAY, Wis. -- Randy Berry had 19 points and 11 rebounds Tuesday night to lift Wisconsin-Green Bay past Cleveland State 74-57. The Phoenix (18-10, 10-6) trailed 32-26 at the break. Six minutes into the second half, Wisconsin-Green Bay was ahead 41-39 and then went on a 22-2 run over the next seven minutes to put the game away. The big second-half showing -- the Phoenix shot 67 percent from the field (18-for-27) -- lifted Green Bay into third place in the Horizon League, a half-game ahead of Cleveland State (13-14, 9-6). The Phoenix finished at 53 percent shooting for the night while the Vikings made just 33 percent in the second half and finished at 41 percent. Rahmon Fletcher scored 17 points and Bryquis Perine had 14 points and eight rebounds for Green Bay. Jeremy Montgomery and Aaron Pogue had 12 points each for the Vikings. Trevon Harmon added 10.
